</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## 📌 Project Objective</span></span><span>
To build a hierarchical file system using a SQL table and calculate the total size of each folder including all nested contents using recursion.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## 🧱 Database Structure</span></span><span>

| Column     | Description                              |
|------------|------------------------------------------|
| NodeID     | Unique identifier for each file/folder   |
| NodeName   | Name of the file or folder               |
| ParentID   | Parent folder ID (NULL if root)          |
| SizeBytes  | Size in bytes (NULL if it's a folder)    |

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## 🧠 Logic</span></span><span>
We use a Recursive CTE to traverse all child nodes for each folder and sum their sizes.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## 🗃️ Files</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`FileSystem_Schema.sql`</span></span><span>: Creates table
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`FileSystem_Data.sql`</span></span><span>: Inserts test data
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`FileSystem_Query.sql`</span></span><span>: Recursive SQL logic
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`Sample_Output.csv`</span></span><span>: Expected result
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`Diagram/`</span></span><span>: Optional visuals

